definition: to circle/to go back/to turn around/to answer/to return/to revolve/Hui ethnic group (Chinese Muslims)/time/classifier for acts of a play/section or chapter (of a classic book)
to (a place)/until (a time)/up to/to go/to arrive/(verb complement denoting completion or result of an action)

sentences.english: She tries to back track, but the President simply walks away.
sentences.chinese: 她试图重新回到话题，但总统一言不发地走开了。

sentences.english: She returned to the hearth, and frankly extended her hand.
sentences.chinese: 她又回到炉边，坦率地伸出她的手。

sentences.english: I need to get back in shape.
sentences.chinese: 我要减回到原来的身材。

sentences.english: When she came back, she did her summer exercise first.
sentences.chinese: 当她回到家中之后，她首先做了暑假作业。

sentences.english: I want to go back to the Flock, of course.
sentences.chinese: 我当然要回到鸥群里去。

sentences.english: My master went back to his friends and we took the boat out to sea.
sentences.chinese: 主人回到他的朋友们那儿去了，我们坐船出了海。

sentences.english: So the salmon that return here are fish that were released from here.
sentences.chinese: 所以回到这里的三文鱼都是我们以前从这里放生的。

sentences.english: I think we should go into the cave.
sentences.chinese: 我觉得我们还是回到那个山洞。

sentences.english: It's not like we're back in Ontario, how's that?
sentences.chinese: 这不像是回到了安大略湖，怎么会？

sentences.english: Please resume your seats, as the performance will continue in two minutes.
sentences.chinese: 请回到你们的座位上，表演两分钟后将继续进行。

sentences.english: She was glad to be on land again.
sentences.chinese: 她很高兴又回到陆地了。

sentences.english: After the war, Reich returned to Salzburg.
sentences.chinese: 战后，雷克回到了萨尔斯堡。

sentences.english: Returns the home to be told grandma, grandma said to buy new?
sentences.chinese: 回到家就告诉奶奶，奶奶说要买新的吗？

sentences.english: He has been pressing to return to China to advocate for greater cultural and religious freedoms for his followers.
sentences.chinese: 他一直努力回到天朝为他的信徒争取文化和总角子有。

sentences.english: They don't want to arrive home to a needy mother, she says.
sentences.chinese: 他们不希望回到家来又看到妈妈穷困疲惫。

sentences.english: Those who have gone back to non-industrialized sections of the country will not be net consumers at all.
sentences.chinese: 那些回到农村的人将不再是净消费者。

definition: to circle/to go back/to turn around/to answer/to return/to revolve/Hui ethnic group (Chinese Muslims)/time/classifier for acts of a play/section or chapter (of a classic book)
to return to/to come (or go) back
to set foot on/to step on or into
(located) at/(to be) in/to exist/in the middle of doing sth/(indicating an action in progress)
